==English==
===Etymology===
Coined by [[singer]] [[w:Justin_Timberlake|Justin Timberlake]] in [[w:2004|2004]] to explain [[w:Super Bowl XXXVIII halftime show controversy|the incident during Super Bowl XXXVIII]] in which [[w:Janet_Jackson|Janet Jackson]]'s right [[breast]] was unintentionally bared.  The first reported instance occurred on ''[[w:The Price Is Right|The Price Is Right]]'' in [[w:1977|1977]], involving contestant Yolanda Bowsley, but the event was not called by this term at the time.

===Noun phrase===
'''[[wardrobe]] [[malfunction]]''' (''plural'' '''wardrobe malfunctions''')

#(''[[euphemistic]]'') An accidental instance of [[indecent exposure]] caused by a fault in someone's [[clothing]] (especially that of a performer) or by an error made while changing this costume.

